reviews.text: Yesterday I had coffee at a Starbucks in Aberdeen Centre. The environment was excellent, I ordered a cup of cold caramel coffee. The coffee didn't taste very strong because they added very little coffee powder but very much milk. This coffee was not good to drink. Besides, I saw that some people who did not buy food but took up the seats.

Nice and small Starbucks coffee place. Probably the only staba I have ever come to with seating available at the moment.
Barista was nice and professional.
Cyberport Hongkong Starbucks: recommend if you are looking for a coffee/ tea/ treats. Clean, good service,  good view,

This has got to be one of the nicest (and most isolated) Starbucks. 
This coffee shop is located in the Cyberport mall on level 2 (i think) it's quite a maze. 
There is minimal seating, but comfortable to say the least. The view was of the street and the buildings opposite, but not to bad in my books 
Prices were of ok value, and the staff were more than friendly

The quality is not consistent with the Starbucks in town. Not sure if it is due to the problem of the franchisee or it is running in a sub standard way because of the fact that lack of competition in the area. 
They are however not the party to be blamed as the whole cyberport was planned, approved and executed by a government of sub standard back then (btw, it still is).
